# Git Conventions

Repository: github.com/lineage-foundation/platform. All git-related text (commits, branches, PRs, issues) in English.

## Commit Messages

Follow [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/):

```
<type>[optional scope]: <description>

[optional body]
[optional footer]
```

**Types:** `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `style`, `refactor`, `perf`, `test`, `chore`, `ci`, `build`

**Scope:** Component affected (e.g., `terraform`, `helm`, `ci`, `platform`).

**Description:** Imperative, present tense, lowercase, no trailing period.

**Examples:** `feat(auth): add login with Google` · `fix(api): handle null response`

## Branch Naming

```
<type>/<short-description>
<type>/<ticket>-<short-description>
```

Examples: `feat/add-google-auth`, `fix/PROJ-123-handle-null-responses`

## Workflow

- Protected: `main` (or `master`). No direct commits.
- Use feature branches and Pull Requests.
- Squash commits when merging. Require reviews.

## Pull Request Creation

When creating a PR after pushing a feature branch, use the **GitHub MCP** `create_pull_request` tool if available. Ensure the GitHub MCP server is configured globally (`~/.cursor/mcp.json`) with `GITHUB_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN` in your environment. Fallback: share the compare URL for manual PR creation.
